reviewText:
I like this movie. But I also have always liked
 Fairuza Balk.

I've always liked weird movies and this one is very weird. The acting is very good but the story is a bit ridiculous. There is just something about this movie that appeals to me, can't really explain it. Seen it at least 6 times already, wouldn't mind seeing it again.

I had never heard of this movie until I saw it listed on my Will Patton search.  As one of our greatest, underrated actors, anything he does is well worth watching (even in the smallest roles.) This was actually a fun movie; I was pleasantly surprised.
Is this the movie, filmed on Big Pine Key, at the Old Wooden Bridge Fishing Camp, mentioned in Tim Dorsey's book, "Florida Roadkill: A Survival Guide,"  p. 40?
